      "description": "One-loop massive box integral family for $gg \\to HH$ in the $m_H=0$ approximation and high-energy limit ($m_t^2 \\ll s,t$). All 4 internal propagators carry top quark mass $m_t$. Results expanded in small $m_t^2$ to $\\mathcal{O}(m_t^{16})$ for the amplitude, expressed in terms of harmonic polylogarithms. Crossings $D_2 = D_1(p_1,p_2,p_4,p_3)$ and $D_3 = D_1(p_1,p_4,p_3,p_2)$ define two additional one-loop families. Integration measure: $(\\mu^2)^{(4-d)/2} e^{\\varepsilon \\gamma_E} d^d k / (i \\pi^{d/2})$. The 10 one-loop master integrals (across $D_1, D_2, D_3$) are listed in Eq. (A.1).",
